{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3424a621-ca59-4f28-8d76-1349c07b8070","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as \"skipped\" in results rather than silently passing or failing, and the reason string appears in test reports.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cafbac09-20df-41b6-971d-f14d95f40960","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to invoke tools or skills.","outputTokens":229,"requestId":"E3C3:229C6C:168E62A:194D3DF:6A0523D5"},"id":"f155c2de-3e63-425a-ab2f-f2dfd82607fb","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:22:35.702Z","parentId":"7519edd5-acdc-4dde-ac7e-961a107dfd46"}
